1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:06,160
Tom, why did you invite monks?

2
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:08,360
Didn’t Win say this house is haunted?

3
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,280
Then please go all out, Father.

4
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:15,160
You again?

5
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,960
You followed me all the way to my house?

6
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,040
I’m going to report you…

7
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:21,040
- Hey, hey!
- Get out of my house!

8
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:23,600
No... please don’t kick me out.

9
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:25,880
I really am the owner of this house.

10
00:00:25,880 --> 00:00:28,160
- I really live here, I…
- Fine, you can stay.

11
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:30,480
But we need to agree on some conditions first.

12
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:32,080
Wanneung.

13
00:00:32,080 --> 00:00:34,920
I can’t sleep when the power’s out.
Let me sleep with you.

14
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:54,880
The electricity should
be back this morning, right?

15
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,600
Last night…

16
00:01:58,080 --> 00:01:59,880
The AC was freezing, huh?

17
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,400
I’m gonna take a shower.

18
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,080
My shoes…

19
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,080
Oh.

20
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:52,280
Why are my cheeks so red?

21
00:04:31,470 --> 00:04:35,110
Excuse me, I’m crossing the line
to grab something from the fridge.

22
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:06,470
Oh no, I overcooked the fried egg.

23
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:08,710
Guess I’ll have to toss it and make a new one.

24
00:05:09,190 --> 00:05:11,990
Hey, hey, no need to make a new one.

25
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:13,870
That’d just be a waste.

26
00:05:13,870 --> 00:05:15,870
Do you know what food waste is?

27
00:05:15,910 --> 00:05:17,790
I’ll help you eat it.

28
00:05:19,910 --> 00:05:21,070
It’s nothing, really.

29
00:05:21,110 --> 00:05:23,310
I just hate wasting food.

30
00:05:26,110 --> 00:05:27,310
Thank you.

31
00:05:30,110 --> 00:05:32,390
Mmm, smells so good.

32
00:05:33,670 --> 00:05:34,710
Wait…

33
00:05:36,710 --> 00:05:39,790
Didn’t you say you wouldn’t throw it away?

34
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:42,910
You’ve got more sides?

35
00:05:44,190 --> 00:05:46,590
Can I get some bacon too?

36
00:05:48,710 --> 00:05:49,870
Thank you.

37
00:05:49,910 --> 00:05:53,910
I promise I’ll finish every last bite.

38
00:06:05,790 --> 00:06:08,990
Hey... how did you know I like

39
00:06:08,990 --> 00:06:11,390
my fried eggs well done like this?

40
00:06:11,710 --> 00:06:14,310
I like them a little crispy like this.

41
00:06:14,710 --> 00:06:16,990
Your bacon is really good.

42
00:06:26,070 --> 00:06:27,590
Hello, Mom.

43
00:06:28,190 --> 00:06:30,070
Win’s been pretty busy lately,

44
00:06:30,110 --> 00:06:31,910
so I haven’t stopped by.

45
00:06:31,990 --> 00:06:33,310
Today?

46
00:06:34,390 --> 00:06:36,910
Okay, I’ll drop by the house.

47
00:06:37,790 --> 00:06:39,110
Alright. Bye.

48
00:06:59,510 --> 00:07:00,510
You…

49
00:07:00,510 --> 00:07:02,110
What are you doing in my car?

50
00:07:02,590 --> 00:07:05,470
Well... you’re heading to Bang Bua Thong, right?

51
00:07:05,510 --> 00:07:07,590
I’ve got work around there anyway.

52
00:07:07,590 --> 00:07:09,510
Can I get a ride with you?

53
00:07:09,790 --> 00:07:11,470
Please... Win?

54
00:07:11,510 --> 00:07:14,190
Please, pretty please...

55
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:18,950
I really need to save money right now.

56
00:07:18,990 --> 00:07:22,790
I have to pay the electricity bill this month
because I lost that bet to you.

57
00:07:24,310 --> 00:07:25,510
Wait a second…

58
00:07:26,710 --> 00:07:29,190
How did you know I’m going to Bang Bua Thong?

59
00:07:29,670 --> 00:07:31,910
Well... you’re going to see your mom, right?

60
00:07:32,110 --> 00:07:33,790
I asked ChatGPT.

61
00:07:33,790 --> 00:07:35,590
Your mom’s house is around there.

62
00:07:36,590 --> 00:07:38,190
Come on, you’ll be late.

63
00:07:38,230 --> 00:07:39,710
Didn’t you make plans with your mom?

64
00:07:39,790 --> 00:07:40,950
Let’s go, hurry.

65
00:07:40,990 --> 00:07:43,390
What is this? You’re unbelievable.

66
00:07:43,710 --> 00:07:45,510
So annoying. Get out.

67
00:07:47,910 --> 00:07:50,110
Didn’t you say you’d let me come?

68
00:07:50,590 --> 00:07:51,790
Get out.

69
00:07:52,710 --> 00:07:56,270
Win, please let me come with you.

70
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:58,190
Get out and close the gate.

71
00:08:00,990 --> 00:08:01,990
Okay.

72
00:08:02,710 --> 00:08:05,110
Let’s call it payment for the ride.

73
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,200
Win.

74
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,480
Wait.

75
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:09,080
Hello, May.

76
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:11,080
I need to talk to you.

77
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,880
With... me?

78
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,200
Who dropped you off just now?

79
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:24,680
- A friend.
- Don’t lie. That was Win, wasn’t it?

80
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,680
Hold on.

81
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,760
All this time,

82
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:33,200
you’ve never cared about someone like me.

83
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,960
But today, you suddenly want to talk.

84
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,040
Is it because you think the one who dropped me off

85
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:39,760
So was Win Pawee?

86
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:41,400
Was it?

87
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,960
Well... Was it...??

88
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,760
Was it...?

89
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:47,480
You’re just an extra, right?

90
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,960
- Yes.
- You can go change now.

91
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Okay.

92
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,440
May, please wait a moment.

93
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:57,080
They’re almost done setting the scene and lights.

94
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,200
Alright.

95
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,600
Excuse me.

96
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:04,160
Wrap is at 4 PM today, right?
I have something after this.

97
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,280
Yes.

98
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:06,570
Thank you.

99
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:31,980
Mom made a lot of your favorite dishes.

100
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:34,880
Put it in the fridge,
so you can heat it up when you’re hungry.

101
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:37,440
You’ve gotten so skinny lately.

102
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:39,280
Haven’t you been eating, sweetie?

103
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:36,360
So… I ran out of stuff,

104
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:38,840
so I borrowed some of yours to eat.

105
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:41,360
But I’ll go buy some to replace it.

106
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,640
I’m sorry.

107
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:45,200
I’ll really go buy it back, I promise.

108
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:10,360
About getting Win to star in the film,

109
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,800
I haven’t decided yet.

110
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:15,040
Waanwaan introduced another kid to me,

111
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:16,240
her name’s Gam.

112
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:18,280
I think she’s interesting.

113
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:20,360
She’s still fresh,

114
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,680
hasn’t been overexposed yet.

115
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,280
But seriously,

116
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:27,360
if you get Win and May as a pair
and I direct,

117
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:30,480
the credit looks way better
than casting a no-name kid.

118
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:33,360
And besides, didn’t you say

119
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:34,960
the role is tough?

120
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,760
If you cast someone inexperienced,

121
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:39,480
you’ll just tire yourself out.

122
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,200
Well…

123
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:45,160
I did contact Win,
but she hasn’t replied yet.

124
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,480
Then I’ll reach out to her.

125
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:06,320
(May)

126
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:14,880
Hello, May.

127
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:16,360
Hi, Win.

128
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:18,360
Director Tong wants to talk to you.

129
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:20,000
He’s on the line right now.

130
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:21,480
Uh…

131
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:27,600
Hello, P’Tong.

132
00:13:28,790 --> 00:13:30,480
Meedee, about the vitamins I asked you to buy,

133
00:13:30,780 --> 00:13:32,070
you can keep them for now.

134
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:34,050
I’ll drop by the hospital to get them later.

135
00:13:34,140 --> 00:13:34,930
Talk later.

136
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:54,380
Wow, that’s a lot of stuff,
Sup'tar Win Pawee.

137
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:57,390
You bought so much.

138
00:13:57,700 --> 00:14:00,070
There’s no way you can finish all that alone.

139
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:01,900
It’ll expire first.

140
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:04,540
I’ll help you eat it then.

141
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:08,000
Just so it doesn’t expire.
Not that I want to eat it or anything.

142
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:18,360
You… why did you buy so much stuff?

143
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:20,760
It’s going to expire, you know.

144
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:22,960
I… I didn’t mean to.

145
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:25,000
I mean, you bought…

146
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:33,600
What’s wrong with her?

147
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:55,000
What’s wrong?

148
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,070
Who’s here?

149
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:07,740
Is it your fan?

150
00:15:08,020 --> 00:15:09,910
Or maybe a sasaeng?

151
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:14,600
Or did some news about you leak,
so reporters followed you here?

152
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,200
Go check it out.

153
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:19,280
I suddenly need to pee.

154
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:22,680
- Go check for me.
- Me?

155
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:25,240
Is that a good idea?
Isn’t this your house?

156
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:27,040
- I’ll pay this month’s electricity bill.
- For real?

157
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:30,040
- For real.
- And… the stuff in the fridge?

158
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:31,240
Can I eat it?

159
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:33,560
You sneak some all the time anyway.

160
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:34,840
Why even ask?

161
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:36,960
I only eat the ones near expiry.

162
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,640
I told you, I hate food waste.

163
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:41,680
You’re the one who keeps buying too much.

164
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:43,360
Go check already. Hurry.

165
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:47,200
- Go.
- Should I really go…?

166
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:48,560
Wanneung.

167
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:51,240
If you’re not going to be useful,

168
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:53,280
then pack your things and leave my house.

169
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,480
I can call the village security.

170
00:15:56,880 --> 00:16:00,960
We’re… housemates living together.

171
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:04,000
We should help each other.
Fine, I’ll go check.

172
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:17,240
Meedee? What are you doing here?

173
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:20,240
Why did you take so long?
What were you doing?

174
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:23,040
Meedee, I was in the bathroom just now.

175
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:24,280
I just finished.

176
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,600
The vitamins.

177
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:29,760
I told you not to come.

178
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:31,400
I was going to pick them up at the hospital.

179
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:32,600
Seriously, you…

180
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:34,640
I called you earlier,

181
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:36,600
but you hung up first.

182
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:39,800
Take the vitamins.

183
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:41,200
So you won’t get sick.

184
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:43,240
Thanks. Thank you.

185
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,280
Wait…

186
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:46,080
Are you kicking me out already?

187
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:48,200
Aren’t you going to invite me in?

188
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:51,880
If you treat me like this, I’ll feel hurt.

189
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,240
Since when do friends feel hurt like that?

190
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:56,280
Come on, Meedee. You should go.

191
00:16:57,680 --> 00:17:00,000
I’m really hungry.

192
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:01,960
Let me eat with you.

193
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:04,280
I haven’t eaten anything since my shift ended.

194
00:17:05,060 --> 00:17:05,740
Or…

195
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:08,480
are you going to fry me an egg here?

196
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:15,400
My treat. There’s a made-to-order
place at the end of the alley.

197
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:16,760
Just go, Meedee.

198
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:17,960
Come with me.

199
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,760
Here she goes again.

200
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,440
I can’t deal with this, Meedee.

201
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,960
Take the vitamins too.

202
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,160
So you won’t get diarrhea.

203
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,560
- Okay, okay.
- Give it back.

204
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:29,080
Bye-bye, Meedee. I’m done.

205
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:30,160
Bye-bye.

206
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,800
Bye, Meedee.

207
00:17:49,320 --> 00:17:50,720
Wanneung

208
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,280
What were you doing over there?

209
00:17:54,360 --> 00:17:55,640
Has she left?

210
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:57,600
Yeah, she’s gone.

211
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:08,000
So who was it?

212
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:11,400
My friend. She dropped something off.

213
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:13,640
Your friend?

214
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:16,040
You knew your friend was coming.

215
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:17,480
Why didn’t you tell me?

216
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,680
That’s cheating.

217
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:22,280
Fine, I’m not paying the electricity bill this month.

218
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:34,440
I’ve only got a little over a thousand baht left.

219
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:36,160
That has to last all month.

220
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:38,560
If you still force me to pay the bill,

221
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,240
I won’t be able to come up with it.

222
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:42,080
Your house will get cut off.

223
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:45,800
Or…

224
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:48,640
do you want to stay in the dark,

225
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:51,440
all creepy at night,

226
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:52,960
and let ghosts haunt you?

227
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,080
Wanneung.

228
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:07,200
Did you turn Director Tong down

229
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,320
because of May?

230
00:20:08,320 --> 00:20:10,400
Think it through first. Don’t rush it.

231
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:13,520
He said you still have time to decide.

232
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:15,440
What are you doing?

233
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:26,080
I’m not doing anything.

234
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:30,440
I’m not reading the message
your girlfriend sent you… either.

235
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:38,040
Win…

236
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:40,040
are you mad at me?

237
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:42,240
I’m sorry.

238
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:45,440
Can you get up now?

239
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:47,000
Get up from what?

240
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:13,200
Did you…

241
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:15,040
have a fight with your girlfriend?

242
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:19,400
This morning, she asked about you too.

243
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:22,720
She was surprised you drove me to the set.

244
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:25,600
But I didn’t say anything.

245
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:29,520
I don’t meddle in other people’s
personal business. You know that.

246
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:33,120
May isn’t my girlfriend.

247
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:34,840
We’re just friends.

248
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,240
But earlier…

249
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:44,120
We can’t love each other.

250
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:47,320
We’re too different.

251
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:50,320
I’m just someone worthless.

252
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:53,120
I could never reach up
to love someone like you.

253
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:55,640
Don’t look down on yourself.

254
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:58,920
We’re just ordinary people.

255
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:01,120
Why can’t we love each other?

256
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:10,840
No.

257
00:22:11,640 --> 00:22:13,000
This isn’t right.

258
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,800
If anyone finds out,

259
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:17,280
it won’t look good.

260
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:18,400
Love…

261
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:19,920
there’s no right or wrong.

262
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:23,040
There’s only love or not love.

263
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,840
For me…

264
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:30,720
you’re the one I love.

265
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:33,840
I love you.

266
00:22:48,120 --> 00:22:49,120
What’s wrong?

267
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:08,920
Why are your face and ears all red?

268
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:12,240
You’re blushing over just a movie?

269
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:27,400
I’m sleepy.

270
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:29,640
I’m going to bed.

271
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:32,640
Sleepy.

272
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:55,520
Hey, who are you?

273
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:58,120
How did you get into my friend’s house?

274
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:00,640
Well…

275
00:24:00,720 --> 00:24:03,440
- I…
- Tom.

276
00:24:04,120 --> 00:24:07,080
- You’re back?
- Yeah, just got home.

277
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:08,320
So I dropped by.

278
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:10,280
I brought the script too.

279
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:11,720
In case you want to read it.

280
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:15,000
I already said I’m not doing it.

281
00:24:15,040 --> 00:24:17,400
Come on… just read it first.

282
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:19,040
It’s really good.

283
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:32,920
By the way…

284
00:24:33,320 --> 00:24:34,920
who is this woman?

285
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:38,080
The former owner.

286
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:41,040
She’s staying temporarily
while looking for a new place.

287
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:43,640
And you’re letting her stay?

288
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:45,320
What if she’s a scammer?

289
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:47,320
Why do you trust people so easily?

290
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,320
Hey…

291
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:51,120
watch your words.

292
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:52,680
Do I look like a thief?

293
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:54,800
I’m dressed this cute.

294
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:57,400
Look at my blue plaid outfit.

295
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:01,200
You’re tiny as a puppy.

296
00:25:01,240 --> 00:25:03,040
One throw and you’d pass out.

297
00:25:03,120 --> 00:25:05,000
So clumsy too.

298
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:06,880
You wouldn’t make it as a thief.

299
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:09,440
You can barely take care of yourself.

300
00:25:09,720 --> 00:25:11,240
Win…

301
00:25:12,520 --> 00:25:14,520
don’t underestimate me.

302
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:18,720
Rule number one: no crossing the line.

303
00:25:38,320 --> 00:25:40,560
- Cut. Scene twenty-one.
- Yes.

304
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,520
Okay… hold for a second.

305
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,840
Memorize your lines.

306
00:25:55,840 --> 00:25:56,840
Hey, you.

307
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:00,800
My name’s P’Man.

308
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:02,040
I’m a modeling agent.

309
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:06,720
Have you signed with anyone yet?

310
00:26:07,240 --> 00:26:08,720
Interested in signing with me?

311
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:11,120
Really?

312
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,920
You’re interested in me?

313
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:15,640
You’re not lying, right?

314
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:19,080
Of course not. Why would I lie?

315
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:21,240
Everyone on this set knows me.

316
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:24,640
Okay. I believe you.

317
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:28,680
So if I’m interested, what do I have to do?

318
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:30,680
Let’s exchange LINE first.

319
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:33,120
- Then you…
- Wanneung.

320
00:26:33,120 --> 00:26:34,560
Wanneung.

321
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,120
Tomorrow,

322
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:38,400
come to my company’s address.

323
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:40,440
We’ll do a screen test.

324
00:26:41,120 --> 00:26:42,960
Someone like you…

325
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:45,960
you’ll definitely get the job.

326
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:47,880
Yes, P’Man.

327
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:51,840
Here’s my LINE.

328
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:54,720
Okay.

329
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:18,440
Tom knows

330
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:20,240
you’re still hurting.

331
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:22,240
From what May did to you.

332
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:24,880
And you probably haven’t forgotten.

333
00:27:27,400 --> 00:27:28,760
If you know that,

334
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:32,560
- why are you still pushing me to act with her?
- Win.

335
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:35,760
Separate work from personal stuff.

336
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:38,040
This is a great opportunity.

337
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:40,840
For you to rebuild your name.

338
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:42,440
I don’t want that.

339
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:45,160
I just want my own life.

340
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,960
Fame, to me…

341
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:49,840
it doesn’t matter anymore.

342
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:53,040
But someone like May won’t give up easily.

343
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:54,760
You know that.

344
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:56,080
If May

345
00:27:56,520 --> 00:27:58,360
wants something,

346
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:06,240
Then you’ll have to be firm about this.

347
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:16,920
Win…

348
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:22,000
Why are you smiling like that?
Did you win the lottery?

349
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:23,760
Even better than that.

350
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:25,880
I’m about to become an actress.

351
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:28,200
Someone wants to sign me as their artist.

352
00:28:28,200 --> 00:28:30,760
I’m about to be famous.
I’m just excited.

353
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:33,920
You really want to be an actress, huh?

354
00:28:34,040 --> 00:28:35,200
Of course, Win.

355
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:37,640
I’ve only ever had one dream.

356
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:39,360
To become a superstar.

357
00:28:39,400 --> 00:28:42,200
I want fame, I want people to love me.

358
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:44,000
I want people to admire me.

359
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:46,760
And now my dream is finally coming true.

360
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:48,760
I’m really excited, Win.

361
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:56,760
How about this…

362
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:58,800
go get dressed up,

363
00:28:58,840 --> 00:29:00,440
I’ll take you out to celebrate.

364
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:03,880
Go get dressed.

365
00:29:03,920 --> 00:29:05,800
I’ll take you to dinner.
You coming or not?

366
00:29:05,840 --> 00:29:07,160
Dinner?

367
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:08,920
Let’s go.

368
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:20,400
If you’re planning something,
just say it.

369
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:23,360
You’re smarter than I thought.

370
00:29:58,120 --> 00:30:00,660
Is there something special
about you asking me out today?

371
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:06,080
I want to talk to you.

372
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:07,640
About what?

373
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:10,080
About us.

374
00:30:10,320 --> 00:30:11,960
About us?

375
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:15,040
What do you mean?

376
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:18,080
You should stop contacting me.

377
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:20,840
There’s no point.

378
00:30:21,240 --> 00:30:23,680
When I’m hurt, I remember.
You know that.

379
00:30:23,840 --> 00:30:24,960
Win…

380
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:26,520
I understand.

381
00:30:26,520 --> 00:30:28,600
I know I was wrong, but…

382
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:31,480
- I just want another chance.
- And about the movie…

383
00:30:36,320 --> 00:30:37,440
The movie.

384
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:41,080
You’ve read the script, right?
Are you taking it?

385
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:42,400
I haven’t read it.

386
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:44,360
And I don’t plan to.

387
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:45,480
Win…

388
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:47,760
This is serious.

389
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:51,280
I talked to the director
to get you this role.

390
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:54,160
And everyone wants this part.

391
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:57,480
The press launch is coming up soon.

392
00:30:57,520 --> 00:30:59,200
What are you waiting for?

393
00:30:59,520 --> 00:31:01,720
Why do you want me to play this role so badly?

394
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:04,600
Because it’ll make you famous again.

395
00:31:04,640 --> 00:31:06,360
And more importantly…

396
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:08,800
I want to do this movie with you.

397
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:10,160
I don’t want to.

398
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:11,840
I don’t want to be famous again.

399
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:13,280
And most importantly…

400
00:31:14,240 --> 00:31:16,000
I don’t want to act with you.

401
00:31:16,520 --> 00:31:19,840
Win… why can’t we even talk properly?

402
00:31:22,520 --> 00:31:24,080
Have you been waiting long?

403
00:31:26,440 --> 00:31:27,680
You…

404
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:32,280
H-Hi, Khun May.

405
00:31:35,120 --> 00:31:36,560
Let’s go.

406
00:31:37,040 --> 00:31:40,200
Oh? I thought we were celebrating here.

407
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:41,400
Better not.

408
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:43,560
The vibe’s not great anymore.

409
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,240
I’ll get going, May.

410
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:19,080
Let’s go.

411
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:20,560
You…

412
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:22,400
What is this?

413
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:24,560
You made me dress up for this place?

414
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:27,560
I thought we were having some fancy dinner.

415
00:32:29,560 --> 00:32:30,960
So…

416
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:33,920
What’s going on between you and May?

417
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,400
I’m so confused.

418
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:38,680
I thought you said you don’t meddle
in other people’s business.

419
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:41,880
Then you don’t need to know.

420
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:44,560
As for what I asked you to do today…

421
00:32:44,640 --> 00:32:46,360
you did great. That’s enough.

422
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:49,960
Wait, wait…

423
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:52,240
You’re leaving already?

424
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:53,840
Yeah.

425
00:32:53,920 --> 00:32:57,160
But I haven’t eaten yet. I’m starving.

426
00:32:57,720 --> 00:33:00,760
Then pick a place you like.
I’ll take you there.

427
00:33:01,320 --> 00:33:04,360
Are you sure you want me to choose?

428
00:33:25,640 --> 00:33:27,680
This is my favorite place.

429
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:32,760
You said you’d let me pick.

430
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:34,480
You…

431
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:36,400
You brought me here?

432
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:38,240
Everyone’s going to recognize me.

433
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:42,040
No. I’m not doing this.

434
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:44,760
Hey, wait. Sit down first.

435
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:46,920
You’ve got sunglasses and a hat in your car, right?

436
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:48,440
Go get them.

437
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:50,480
Wear sunglasses and a hat now?

438
00:33:50,840 --> 00:33:52,560
Wouldn’t that make me stand out more?

439
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:56,520
You said I could choose the place.

440
00:33:56,520 --> 00:33:58,800
And I just helped you with May.

441
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:01,000
And I’m really hungry right now.

442
00:34:01,040 --> 00:34:02,520
If I don’t eat,

443
00:34:02,560 --> 00:34:04,200
I might get sick.

444
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:05,720
End up bedridden.

445
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:08,280
And I have a screen test tomorrow.

446
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:10,280
Fine, but…

447
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:11,600
Eat fast and we leave.

448
00:34:11,640 --> 00:34:12,640
Okay?

449
00:34:12,800 --> 00:34:13,880
Okay?

450
00:34:16,240 --> 00:34:18,360
Miss, can we get a menu?

451
00:34:22,640 --> 00:34:23,760
What would you like?

452
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:27,480
One papaya salad with
fermented fish and crab, please.

453
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:30,920
Extra chili.
Make it super spicy and rich, please.

454
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:32,440
One grilled pork.

455
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,880
One grilled chicken and one sticky rice.

456
00:34:34,920 --> 00:34:37,160
- Do you want anything?
- No.

457
00:34:37,640 --> 00:34:39,040
That’s all for now.

458
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:40,360
The menu, sir.

459
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:47,920
And one plate of Soi Ju as well, please.

460
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:50,480
- Soi Ju?
- Soi Ju.

461
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:02,160
Is this tuna?

462
00:35:03,640 --> 00:35:04,840
Soi Ju.

463
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:06,080
Ever heard of it?

464
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:07,680
Want to try it?

465
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:08,920
Here.

466
00:35:10,720 --> 00:35:12,280
Give it a try.

467
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:14,040
This place is someone’s favorite, you know.

468
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:16,880
I love coming here with my friends.
It’s really good.

469
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:27,680
Here.

470
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:30,840
Eat a lot. I ordered extra for you.

471
00:35:34,040 --> 00:35:35,040
What’s wrong?

472
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:37,960
Weren’t you full earlier?

473
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:46,600
When you pick a restaurant,

474
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:49,360
at least ask if I can actually eat the food.

475
00:36:49,920 --> 00:36:53,040
It’s all good stuff.
How can you not eat it?

476
00:36:58,640 --> 00:37:00,280
You eat like a monster.

477
00:37:05,040 --> 00:37:07,360
So you’re really going back to acting?

478
00:37:10,040 --> 00:37:11,360
I already turned it down.

479
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:13,560
Why, Win?

480
00:37:13,640 --> 00:37:16,800
If it were me, I’d never refuse.

481
00:37:16,840 --> 00:37:19,120
You’re living the life I dream of.

482
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:22,600
Out of nowhere,
someone offers you a great script.

483
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:26,160
You don’t have to run from casting to casting,
getting rejected every day like me.

484
00:37:32,760 --> 00:37:33,960
Do you know,

485
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:36,760
this industry isn’t as beautiful as you think.

486
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:51,040
Where’s the love?

487
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:54,800
I’ve grown up all this time
and never once felt it.

488
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:58,040
I’ve never even heard the word “love.”

489
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:02,120
Even if it’s a lie, I still want to hear it.

490
00:38:02,120 --> 00:38:03,880
You wouldn’t understand

491
00:38:04,040 --> 00:38:06,640
what it’s like growing up alone,

492
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:10,280
with no one who loves you.

493
00:38:11,320 --> 00:38:13,600
But you can’t tell me what love feels like either.

494
00:38:13,640 --> 00:38:15,160
You…

495
00:38:15,200 --> 00:38:16,200
Enough.

496
00:38:16,240 --> 00:38:18,600
Do you even really want to be an actress?

497
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:21,000
I’m being serious right now.

498
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:23,680
And this is how you’d perform for an audience?

499
00:38:23,720 --> 00:38:25,640
Yeah. So what?

500
00:38:26,120 --> 00:38:27,840
No wonder you never pass auditions.

501
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:29,560
Look at the way you act.

502
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:32,000
Why? What’s wrong with how I did it?

503
00:38:32,040 --> 00:38:33,720
What part wasn’t good?

504
00:38:33,720 --> 00:38:36,760
Go on, explain it, Ms. Superstar.

505
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,800
What are you doing?

506
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:44,440
Blocking.

507
00:38:45,520 --> 00:38:47,480
Every part of it was bad.

508
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:51,720
Oh yeah? And you’re so good?
Why do you get to judge me?

509
00:38:51,720 --> 00:38:54,560
I was seriously trying, okay?

510
00:38:58,040 --> 00:38:59,280
Fine. I’ll show you.

511
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:05,720
Where’s the love?

512
00:39:05,920 --> 00:39:07,800
Since the day I was born,

513
00:39:07,840 --> 00:39:10,640
I’ve never once felt it.

514
00:39:10,720 --> 00:39:14,960
I’ve never even heard the word “love.”

515
00:39:15,840 --> 00:39:17,960
Love isn’t just words.

516
00:39:18,720 --> 00:39:21,600
Anyone can lie with words.

517
00:39:24,040 --> 00:39:25,560
Even if it’s a lie,

518
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:27,680
I still want to hear it.

519
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:30,160
You don’t understand

520
00:39:30,240 --> 00:39:32,720
what it’s like growing up alone,

521
00:39:32,720 --> 00:39:34,160
with no one to love you.

522
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:35,760
You wouldn’t get it.

523
00:39:51,520 --> 00:39:53,800
You’re not alone, though.

524
00:39:58,880 --> 00:39:59,920
But…

525
00:40:00,520 --> 00:40:03,080
you still can’t tell me

526
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:06,080
what love really feels like.

527
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:10,480
Have you ever loved someone that much?

528
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:14,360
Yes.

529
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:17,880
What was it like?

530
00:40:18,440 --> 00:40:20,680
Tell me.

531
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:25,000
It’s a feeling inside.

532
00:40:25,040 --> 00:40:26,760
You can’t really put it into words.

533
00:40:30,520 --> 00:40:31,840
Then…

534
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:34,760
how do you make them know

535
00:40:35,120 --> 00:40:37,880
that you love them?

536
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:42,560
Well…

537
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:51,960
Like this.

538
00:41:33,120 --> 00:41:35,080
That’s good acting.

539
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:38,000
Good acting

540
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:42,080
isn’t just memorizing lines
or copying someone else.

541
00:41:42,120 --> 00:41:44,360
It has to come from inside.

542
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:49,160
So?

543
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:51,280
Feel any different?

544
00:41:56,240 --> 00:41:58,160
Then that’s good.

545
00:41:58,920 --> 00:42:00,360
I’m going to shower.

546
00:43:10,920 --> 00:43:12,280
Wanneung.

547
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:16,040
Win?

548
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:18,240
I thought you went to see your friend.

549
00:43:18,600 --> 00:43:21,760
I just stopped to get gas. I’m heading out now.

550
00:43:22,440 --> 00:43:25,440
You’re going to your screen test, right?
Want me to drive you?

551
00:43:28,920 --> 00:43:31,000
You’re not planning anything again, are you?

552
00:43:31,960 --> 00:43:33,280
No.

553
00:43:34,240 --> 00:43:36,840
Or are you going to charge me for gas?

554
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:38,960
I wouldn’t charge you.

555
00:43:48,040 --> 00:43:50,480
You can go.

556
00:44:06,960 --> 00:44:08,040
Turn right here.

557
00:44:08,780 --> 00:44:10,140
You can park right here.

558
00:44:18,180 --> 00:44:20,620
Thanks for the ride, Win.

559
00:44:22,300 --> 00:44:23,460
Can you...

560
00:44:23,460 --> 00:44:25,220
wish me luck?

561
00:44:29,300 --> 00:44:30,820
Do your best.

562
00:44:30,900 --> 00:44:33,220
And I hope you succeed.

563
00:44:34,580 --> 00:44:37,140
Amen.

564
00:44:39,980 --> 00:44:41,020
Hey…

565
00:44:41,100 --> 00:44:43,460
Can I borrow your phone to call mine?

566
00:44:43,500 --> 00:44:45,140
I can’t find it.

567
00:44:46,660 --> 00:44:47,940
Sure.

568
00:45:06,180 --> 00:45:07,740
Okay, I’m going now.

569
00:45:08,580 --> 00:45:09,820
Good luck.

570
00:45:10,180 --> 00:45:12,340
Okay.

571
00:45:34,500 --> 00:45:35,940
Hello.

572
00:45:45,860 --> 00:45:46,940
Wanneung...

573
00:45:46,980 --> 00:45:49,020
- Hi.
- Hello.

574
00:45:50,100 --> 00:45:51,180
You came alone?

575
00:45:51,220 --> 00:45:53,820
You told me to come alone, didn’t you?

576
00:45:54,580 --> 00:45:55,620
Good.

577
00:45:55,780 --> 00:45:56,820
So…

578
00:45:56,980 --> 00:45:59,660
You didn’t book anyone else today?

579
00:45:59,900 --> 00:46:01,060
I did.

580
00:46:01,380 --> 00:46:03,620
But I spaced them out.

581
00:46:03,860 --> 00:46:07,660
I wanted Wanneung to have proper time
for a screen test.

582
00:46:07,700 --> 00:46:09,260
So I can pitch it.

583
00:46:09,300 --> 00:46:10,940
People need to see your talent.

584
00:46:11,780 --> 00:46:12,820
Ready?

585
00:46:14,100 --> 00:46:15,540
Yes.

586
00:46:16,180 --> 00:46:17,180
Let’s go.

587
00:46:17,220 --> 00:46:18,620
This way.

588
00:46:19,780 --> 00:46:20,980
Over here.

589
00:46:54,300 --> 00:46:55,940
I’ve got a film script.

590
00:46:55,980 --> 00:46:58,060
The director’s looking for a lead actress.

591
00:46:58,300 --> 00:47:00,140
But the role is a bit sexy.

592
00:47:00,260 --> 00:47:02,300
You’d have to show some skin.

593
00:47:02,700 --> 00:47:04,100
If you’re brave enough,

594
00:47:04,180 --> 00:47:05,620
I’ll give you the lead.

595
00:47:05,980 --> 00:47:07,340
Come on, let’s start.

596
00:47:09,580 --> 00:47:12,740
How sexy are we talking?

597
00:47:18,060 --> 00:47:22,020
You’ll need to take it off
and show me first, to see if you pass.

598
00:47:22,500 --> 00:47:23,740
No.

599
00:47:23,780 --> 00:47:26,980
Why didn’t you tell me
this was that kind of casting?

600
00:47:27,020 --> 00:47:29,100
I won’t take a job like this.

601
00:47:29,180 --> 00:47:30,380
Come on…

602
00:47:30,380 --> 00:47:31,940
You’re already here.

603
00:47:32,300 --> 00:47:33,620
Don’t you want to be famous?

604
00:47:33,980 --> 00:47:36,140
No. I’m leaving.

605
00:47:42,660 --> 00:47:43,900
- Huh…
- Let go.

606
00:47:44,100 --> 00:47:45,420
Wanneung.

607
00:47:45,460 --> 00:47:47,260
- Wanneung.
- Let go.

608
00:47:55,540 --> 00:47:56,540
Wanneung.

609
00:48:01,780 --> 00:48:04,620
- Let go! Let go!
- Stay still!

610
00:48:07,060 --> 00:48:08,500
Let go!

611
00:48:10,740 --> 00:48:11,780
Wanneung.

612
00:48:17,940 --> 00:48:19,580
You bastard!

613
00:48:35,020 --> 00:48:36,380
Are you hurt?

614
00:49:28,620 --> 00:49:29,660
You…

615
00:50:10,020 --> 00:50:11,020
Help!

616
00:51:01,510 --> 00:51:02,370
May…

617
00:51:01,860 --> 00:51:02,820
(NEXT EPISODE Preview)

618
00:51:02,860 --> 00:51:05,020
Can I get Director Tom’s number?

619
00:51:05,060 --> 00:51:06,380
I want to talk to him.

620
00:51:06,420 --> 00:51:09,260
I’ll vouch for her with my name.
She can do it.

621
00:51:09,300 --> 00:51:10,860
And she’s perfect for this role.

622
00:51:10,900 --> 00:51:12,780
You’re an actress now, Wanneung.

623
00:51:12,780 --> 00:51:14,340
Congratulations.

624
00:51:14,380 --> 00:51:18,340
You’re really on your way
to becoming a superstar!

625
00:51:18,340 --> 00:51:19,420
Look at me.

626
00:51:19,420 --> 00:51:22,100
And try to feel what I’m trying to say.

627
00:51:22,460 --> 00:51:25,260
Are you trying to tell me that…

628
00:51:25,940 --> 00:51:29,100
you like me, Win?

629
00:51:34,020 --> 00:51:35,220
How did this person get in?

630
00:51:35,220 --> 00:51:36,860
I’m supposed to sit there.

631
00:51:36,860 --> 00:51:39,540
That seat is Belle’s.

632
00:51:41,260 --> 00:51:42,300
(finally…?)

633
00:51:43,420 --> 00:51:45,020
- Does it suit me?
- What outfit?

634
00:51:45,060 --> 00:51:46,060
What’s the theme?

635
00:51:46,260 --> 00:51:47,740
(Vintage fashion)

636
00:51:49,660 --> 00:51:51,540
(There there, good job)

637
00:51:54,980 --> 00:51:56,060
(Non-stop eating)

638
00:51:56,420 --> 00:51:58,260
Is it spicy? It’s not spicy.

639
00:51:58,300 --> 00:52:01,660
- Why are you crying?
- I’m emotional.
